And for the sake of performance, I recommend the below 5 tasks
(It may already be set up)

1. iommu disable
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="amd_iommu=off iommu=off"

2. setting cpu performance
$ cat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/scaling_governor

# performance setting
$ echo performance | tee /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor

# check
$ cat /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu0/cpufreq/scaling_governor


3. disable hyper threading
$ lscpu | grep -E "Thread|Core"

$ vi /etc/default/grub
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="amd_iommu=off iommu=off nosmt"

$ update-grub
$ reboot now

# check
$ lscpu | grep -E "Thread|Core"

4. install DOCA + HPCX
5. add NFSD_IO_DIRECT option
